<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">AFFIDAVIT OF SANJAY REDDY</TI>
<P>I, SANJAY REDDY, of the City of Brampton, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY:</P>
<P>1. I am an applicant in these proceedings and as such have knowledge of the matters hereinafter deposed. Where that knowledge is based on information obtained from others, I have so indicated and believe that information to be true.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><UNDER>EVIDENCE IN SUPPORT OF BREACH OF CONTRACT</UNDER></TI>
<P>2. On April 30, 2016, I purchased Unit # [#omitted] in Tower A of the Cosmos Tower project. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD> is my agreement of purchase and sale (the &ldquo;Agreement&rdquo;). The Vendor is the respondent 1945086 Ontario Inc.</P>
<P>3. My agreement included a standard 12 page Tarion Condominium Form (the &ldquo;Tarion Addendum&rdquo;) plus page 5B (inserted by the Vendor) entitled &ldquo;Appendix Early Termination Conditions&rdquo; where Condition #2 is set out (the &ldquo;Early Termination Condition #2&rdquo;).</P>
<P>4. I am advised by Kiara Sander (a law clerk at Charney Lawyers PC) and believe that the agreement I signed is a standard form, signed by all applicants in Towers A, B and III which included the Tarion Addendum and the same appendix with Early Termination Condition #2. With respect to Tower III, the Vendor was the respondent 1945087 Ontario Inc.</P>
<P>5. I am advised by Ms. Sander and believe that all applicants signed the Agreement as detailed in Schedule A to the Notice of Application.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><UNDER>THE CANCELLATION</UNDER></TI>
<P>6. On or about April 4<SUP>th</SUP> and 6<SUP>th</SUP>, 2018, I received two letters. I received one from the respondent Liberty Development Corporation and one from the respondents 1945086 Ontario Inc. and 1945087 Ontario Inc., (albeit on Liberty stationary) informing me the project was cancelled. The basis for the cancellation was Early Termination Condition #2. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibits &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> and <BOLD>&ldquo;C&rdquo;</BOLD> are the letters.</P>
<P>7. I am advised by Ms. Sander that all applicants received the same two letters.</P>
<P>8. I am advised by Ms. Sander and believe that Bratty and Partners also mailed a letter to all applicants returning deposits, while reiterating how the vendor exercised its right to terminate the Purchase Agreement in accordance with the Tarion Addendum. A sample of the letter is included here as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>9. I am advised by Ms. Ina Cici, an applicant in this proceeding, and believe that she purchase Unit [#omitted] Tower B of the Cosmos Tower Project on May 5, 2016. Her agreement is attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;E&rdquo;</BOLD>. Ms. Cici received the same cancellation letters as I did.</P>
<P>10. I am advised by Ms. Carla Gravina, an applicant in this proceeding, and believe that she purchased Unit [#omitted] Tower III of the Cosmos Tower Project on October 1, 2016. Her agreement is attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;F&rdquo;</BOLD>. Ms. Gravina received the same cancellation letters as I did.</P>
<P>11. I understand that Tarion has a mandate to provide warranties to Ontario purchasers of new homes and protect consumers who are purchasing new homes. As part of its work in fulfilling its mandate, it publishes information to educate consumers of their rights. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo;</BOLD> is an explanation of the &ldquo;tentative occupancy date&rdquo; requirements under the Tarion Addendum, which includes an explanation of the early termination conditions.</P>
<P>12. I have sustained damages because the project was cancelled. Since 2016 the market price for condominiums in Vaughan has significantly increased. The increase in pre-construction market prices for condominiums in Vaughan is well documented in the news. I have been following the price increases for new pre-construction condominium units. Current sales prices to purchase comparable units pre-construction are much higher now, as indicated in recent studies by industry associations, attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><UNDER>EVIDENCE IN SUPPORT OF LIBERTY DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION AND 1834371 ONTARIO INC. BEING PROPER PARTIES TO THIS PROCEEDING</UNDER></TI>
<P>13. When I was considering purchasing a unit in the Cosmos Tower Project it was being promoted to the public as a Liberty Development project. I recall going to a Liberty Development website where the project was promoted as a Liberty Development project. I attended a presentation center where the centre itself and all of the promotional material characterized the project as a Liberty Development project.</P>
<P>14. For instance, a sketch of my proposed unit includes the Liberty Development trademark/logo with a disclaimer from Liberty Development Corporation &ldquo;All rights reserved&rdquo;. The special preview price list for Tower A includes the same trademark with a slogan &ldquo;LIBERTYforall.ca&rdquo; and a footnote indicating &ldquo;Liberty Development Corporation, 2016. All rights reserved. Brokers protected.&rdquo; The Cosmos Tower A worksheet has the web address for the project <UNDER>www.cosmoscondos.ca</UNDER> but the web site no longer has the promotional information it did at the time the units were for sale. Special Preview Price List for Tower B has the same logo and slogan. These documents are collectively attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>15. I also received a glossy brochure promoting the sale of the units available in Tower A, which was available to all who attended the presentation center. The 62 page brochure includes Liberty Development's logo on the back cover and a description of Liberty's history at page 61 &ldquo;[a]s a leader in forging growth throughout the GTA...&rdquo;as well as a description of industry awards. Page 62 includes images of a number of Liberty projects. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo;</BOLD> are the front and back covers of the brochure and pages 61-62.</P>
<P>16. The applicant Ina Cici has advised me and I believe that she received the same glossy brochure at the presentation centre. She also received a letter dated May 17, 2016, a document entitled Mortgage Approval Requirements and a document entitled &ldquo;Cosmos Condominiums RBC Royal Bank working with Liberty Development&rdquo;, which is a solicitation for mortgage financing. These documents are collectively attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;K&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>17. The applicant Carla Gravina has advised me and I believe that she received a 48 page glossy brochure with the same references to Liberty Developments as in my brochure. Her brochure came in an envelope where the logo for Liberty Development is prominently displayed. She also received a letter dated February 22, 2017 and a special preview price list. The envelope, letter and price list are attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;L&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>18. On the Liberty Development Website, the company provides a company profile which includes a history of its projects and the role of the founders. A print-out of the Company Profile, as of September 13, 2018 is attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;M&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>19. The Corporate Profile Reports for the four respondents are attached as <BOLD>Exhibits &ldquo;N&rdquo;, &ldquo;O&rdquo;, &ldquo;P&rdquo; and &ldquo;Q&rdquo;</BOLD>. The officers and directors of the four respondents are virtually the same. I am advised by Ms. Sander that the searches were conducted on August 1, 2018.</P>
<P>20. Liberty Development is registered with Tarion as an Umbrella Group. As stated by Tarion:
<QUOTE><P>An Umbrella Group is a group of builders sharing at least one common officer, director, principal or partner. It is used by Tarion to identify associated past and current registered builders.</P>
<P>Umbrella Groups are shown in the Builder Directory on Tarion's website to let consumers know other names under which the builder may be operating and the communities in which it builds, and to provide a more complete history of the builder's performance.</P></QUOTE></P>
<P>Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;R&rdquo;</BOLD> is a description of Umbrella Groups and Liberty Development's profile as an Umbrella Group. 1945086 Ontario Inc. and 1945087 Ontario Inc. are listed as member companies of the Liberty Development Umbrella Group.</P>
<P>21. I am advised by Ms. Sander and believe that Charney Lawyers hired a title search company to conduct an abstract search of title to the lands where the Cosmos Towers were to be constructed. The search was conducted on or about July 26, 2018. According to the search results, the municipal addresses for the project in Vaughan included 190 Maplecrest Road; 2951 Highway7 West; and 180 Maplecrest Road. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibits &ldquo;S&rdquo;, &ldquo;T&rdquo;</BOLD> and <BOLD>&ldquo;U&rdquo;</BOLD> are the notes for each search and the abstract.</P>
<P>22. I am advised by Ms. Sander and believe that Charney Lawyers also received a copy of a registered charge/collateral mortgage registered against title to the lands where the project was to be constructed in the amount of 100 million including a Schedule 2 Collateral Mortgage attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;V&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>23. The collateral mortgage refers to an indemnity agreement dated January 13, 2017 between the respondent Vendors and the respondent 1834371 Ontario Inc. By letter dated September 20, 2018 Mr. Charney wrote to counsel requesting a copy of the indemnity agreement and all agreements between Liberty Development Corporation and the respondents. The letter is attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;W&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>24. I understand that the Tarion Addendum to the Agreement of Purchase and Sale includes an arbitration clause at clause 15. The purchasers have concerns about this application proceeding as an arbitration, as set out in a letter sent by Mr. Charney to counsel, dated September 20, 2018, attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;X&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>25. In or about June 2018, Liberty Developments applied to the City of Vaughan for an application to construct a two tower condominium project adjacent to the cancelled Cosmos Tower project at Highway 7 and Maplecrest Road comprised of two towers, 962 units and a seven story mid-rise building. I am aware that a number of the applicants attended the planning committee hearing to voice complaints about this application, Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;Y&rdquo;</BOLD> is a media article and an excerpt of the minutes of the Committee meeting dated May 23, 2018.</P>
<P>26. There have also been recent media articles documenting a Liberty Development announcement that it intends to modernize the Promenade Mall in Vaughan construct new buildings on the lands including three residential apartment towers of 8 to 35 stories with 1006 units as well as offices and a hotel with 15.203 square meters of hotel space and 24,392 square meters of office space. Attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;Z&rdquo;</BOLD> is a media article detailing the Liberty Development announcement.</P>
