<BLOCK1><TI>ORDER</TI>
<P>THIS APPLICATION for an order declaring that Early Termination Condition #2 (&ldquo;Condition #2&rdquo;) in the Tarion Addendum attached to the agreements of purchase and sale between the Applicants, Jay Reddy, Jacob Jaramillo, Carla Gravina, Ina Cici, Cecilia Yung, Santino Paglia, Giuseppe Panza, Mark Cruden, and the Applicants Listed in Schedule A to this Order, and 1945086 Ontario Inc. or 1945087 Ontario Inc. (the &ldquo;Contract&rdquo; or &ldquo;Contracts&rdquo;) is null and void, or alternatively is not enforceable, and for an order that, by cancelling the Contracts based on Condition #2, 1945086 Ontario Inc. and 1945087 Ontario Inc. breached the Contracts was heard April 23, 2019 at the court house, 330 University Avenue, Toronto, Ontario, M5G 1R7.</P>
<P>ON READING the Applicants' Notice of Application, the Application Record, the Responding Application Record, the Reply Application Record, and the written submission of the parties, and on hearing the submission of the lawyers for the parties,</P>
<P>1. THIS COURT ORDERS that this application is dismissed as against all the Respondents without costs.</P>
